    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Be so good as to get my name put down for one copy of each of the maps whose
                    proposals you sent.</p>
                <p>I fling my views into another form. So <persName ref="pe0280">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Philips</persName> &amp; I shall never
                    interfere. Pray let me see his proposals.</p>
                <p>I have got the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0181">leges
                    saxonic√¶</title></bibl>.</p>
                <p>I never yet saw or at lest observed <gap reason="illegible" unit="words" quantity="1"/> seals. It is to be seen in <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>.</p>
                <p>I hope you will think the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0020">Br.
                        Zool.</title></bibl> much improved from the old editions.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Dec<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> 1. 1776.</dateline></closer>

            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> George Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh.</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p><unclear reason="illegible">69</unclear></p>
